{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29bc352e-636c-4c92-9fa0-ff2b330f6bc7","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, VSTest options are replaced by platform-native switches. Platform-specific args go after `--` when using `dotnet test`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Prerequisites** (in your `.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nAnd add the corresponding NuGet packages:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n> **Note:** `--filter` is still handled by `dotnet test` and translated for the platform. Everything after `--` is passed directly to the test runner.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88568279-c377-44c7-b8b0-ebac50bd281b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` becomes `--hangdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nI need to be more precise about the Microsoft.Testing.Platform CLI syntax since it differs from VSTest. The filter syntax and logger options have changed, and I should verify the exact parameter names and formats for the new runner. I need to clarify the .NET version differences here—Microsoft.Testing.Platform is natively supported in .NET 9 with `dotnet test`, but for .NET 8 I'd need to enable it explicitly through project settings like `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` or `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` before the command arguments will work as expected. I'm working through the exact syntax for passing those additional flags through `dotnet test` with the testing platform bridge, and I realize I should just give them the clearest approach: use `dotnet test` with `--filter` for the standard options, then pass the platform-specific arguments like `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, and the dump options after the `--` separator.","outputTokens":1553,"requestId":"042F:13D2B1:1E379CD:220B8F1:69E81A4D"},"id":"7ab2d3fe-7c71-4d54-8eba-5563c5a35301","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:31.242Z","parentId":"d96b171c-5151-4d06-ac9a-3db324ec31f0"}
